prompt:
Add a public class called Calculator to Domain.calr with a public method Add that takes two i32 parameters and returns i32.

Use this exact Calor method in class syntax:
§CL{c001:Calculator:pub}
  §MT{m001:Add:pub}
    §I{i32:a}
    §I{i32:b}
    §O{i32}
    §R (+ a b)
  §/MT{m001}
§/CL{c001}

The §MT{id:name:visibility} syntax defines a method:
- id is a unique method identifier
- name is the method name
- visibility is pub/priv/prot (public/private/protected)
- Methods inside classes use §MT, not §F
